column5: Great report, too bad the fishing was bunk..  At least the scenery was noice!  cheers HD
great adventure!  And that last sunset shot is a real beauty....a memorable trip with or without the fish...nicely done

Correction Wayne...."dogs"  .......it's a blessing I didn't head up with you...we got POUNDED with snow here in the Ottawa Valley!!!....I'm trying to get a plan together to see how we're going to get the ice shacks off the river for the Saturday deadline!!!....doesn't look promising right now!!
Thanks for the report Wayne. Some really nice pics in there too. You're fortunate to be able to get away like that from time to time.
Great shots and read Wayne. Thanks
Good stuff  Wayne and definetely better to be playing in the snow, rather that shovelling it all weekend like most of us
A big thanks, Irish, for yet another glimpse into what I wish I could also do.  It goes to show that fishing can be pretty tough even on these seldom fished remote lakes.
Thanks for sharing the story and the pics.

Nice fishing trip/report wayne !!!!.  ..too bad about loosing a few days being sick,but at least you got to go sledding and hit a few new lakes to explore later on,  and it must have been cool to meet up with all those guys and go ripping around on all those nice machines !!!! better luck next time...cheers
Ahhh man, that sounded like a fun weekend! Great report Wayne  .
Great adventures Wayne.  Another enjoyable Temagami report.
What he said above.  Man I wish I was there!
great post!  thanks for sharing!  i love that area of the province!  cheers!
You know I'd gnaw that tree down for ya bud! Just gotta find the time.
Too much info Wayne!  Let me know when you are going to take that other tree down...I think TJ is free that day!  Great report...looked like a nice few days...well except for that puking thing...LOL.
great report wayne even without (insert laker photo here) fish TB
..oh and I forgot "and having to look after their dog" !  Thanks Steve.. and everyone.
